pare to MD single-bond work of adhesion predictions?\n\n    *   *Status:* All sub-questions have ZERO evidence so far. The read pages are irrelevant to the specific chemistry/substrate combo.\n\n4.  **Identify Contradictions:**\n    *   None yet. Not enough data.\n\n5.  **Ident Knowledge Gaps:**\n    *   Specific adhesion values (N/m or MPa).\n    *   Existence of MD simulations for PEI-DVS interfaces.\n    *   Existence of plasma treatment protocols for PP/Al2O3 in this context.\n    *   Direct comparison studies (Experiment vs. Simulation).\n\n6.  **Perspectives Needed:**\n    *   Scientific (primary literature), Methodological (how adhesion was measured/simulated).\n\n7.  **Draft Queries:**\n    *   Need to target academic databases (even via web search) and specific chemical combinations.\n    *   Web: \"divinyl sulfone polyethylenimine adhesion strength\", \"PEI DVS crosslinked coating polypropylene plasma\", \"molecular dynamics simulation PEI adhesion work of adhesion\".\n    *   Academic: \"divinyl sulfone\" AND \"polyethylenimine\" AND \"adhesion\" AND (\"simulation\" OR \"molecular dynamics\"), \"lap shear\" AND \"polyethylenimine\" AND \"crosslinked\".\n    *   Exa: Semantic search for the specific comparison (experiment vs MD).\n\n8.  **Assess Completeness:**\n    *   Status: 'expanding'. Major sub-questions unanswered.\n    *   Evidence Strength: All weak/non-existent.\n\n9.  **Continuation:**\n    *   Yes, definitely need to continue. The current results are off-target (regulatory vs. scientific).\n\n10. **Construct JSON:**\n    *   Ensure strict JSON validity. Escape quotes. No trailing commas.\n    *   Follow the implied schema based on the prompt's numbered list (though the prompt asks for JSON *containing* the answers to 1-10, I need to structure it logically).\n    *   *Self-Correction on Schema:* The prompt asks me to respond with valid JSON only. It lists 10 tasks. I should structure the JSON keys to reflect these tasks clearly.\n    *   Keys: `