e 3 and Source 7 indicate that the TSCA Chemical Substance Inventory can be searched online via EPA's Substance Registry Services to determine existing status, but the search results provided do not contain the output of such a specific query. Additionally, Source 13 lists submission types like PMNs and SNUNs but does not provide status information for divinyl sulfone specifically. Consequently, the specific regulatory status for this precise application cannot be confirmed from these documents alone, and direct consultation of the TSCA Inventory or specific SNUR listings via EPA databases is required to determine if exemptions exist. Researchers must verify if the specific use constitutes a significant new use requiring notification under the general rules described in Source 11.\", \"key_findings\": [\"CAS 100-44-7 is listed in 40 CFR 716.120 with § 716.20(b)(3) applicability for data reporting.\", \"General SNURs require 90-day EPA notification before manufacture or processing for significant new uses.\", \"Vinyl sulfones generally are not expected to pose significant risk unless water releases are high.\", \"Specific Section 5 exemptions for Al2O3 coatings are not detailed in provided sources.\"], \"sources_used\": [\"https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/chapter-I/subchapter-R/part-716/subpart-B/section-716.120\", \"https://www.epa.gov/tsca-inventory\", \"https://gpcgateway.com/regulatory-regions/usa/regulation/Mg%3D%3D?sector=MQ%3D%3D-chemicals\", \"https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2025/11/04/2025-19773/significant-new-use-rules-on-certain-chemical-substances-24-45e\", \"https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/chapter-I/subchapter-R/part-721\", \"https://www.epa.gov/system/files/documents/2024-02/ncp_chemical_categories.pdf\"]}\n\n    Word count check on 'answer':\n    \"Based on the provided search results, there is insufficient specific information to identify exact TSCA Section 5 exemptions or Significant New Use Rules (SNURs) applicable specifically