does not report thermodynamic adhesion metrics or validation against atomistic binding energy calculations [Source 8].\" (37)\n    \"Other sources discuss DVS crosslinking mechanisms but apply them to different polymers, such as Hyaluronic Acid, where crosslinking performance is evaluated based on chemical modification rather than adhesion thermodynamics [Source 2][Source 5].\" (31)\n    \"Additionally, while there are studies regarding adhesion improvement on polypropylene films involving contact angle measurements to prove enhanced wettability, these involve different modification methods and do not utilize PEI/DVS systems [Source 14][Source 15].\" (32)\n    \"Source 6 describes crosslinked linear PEI systems for DNA delivery, indicating crosslinking research exists but is focused on biomedical delivery rather than surface adhesion mechanics [Source 6].\" (25)\n    \"Furthermore, general adhesion studies between polypropylene and other polymers like nylon 6 or polyethylene utilize reactive compatibilization or co-extrusion, lacking the specific PEI/DVS chemistry required for this validation [Source 11][Source 13].\" (31)\n    \"Consequently, the search results do not adequately answer the question regarding proxy data for validating atomistic calculations.\" (16)\n    \"The specific combination of DVS-crosslinked PEI, thermodynamic work of adhesion measurements, and polypropylene or aluminum oxide substrates is absent from the provided literature.\" (22)\n    \"The absence of inverse gas chromatography data or specific contact angle analysis for this chemical system prevents a direct comparison between molecular dynamics predictions and experimental thermodynamic work of adhesion.\" (26)\n\n    Total: 36+39+37+31+32+25+31+16+22+26 = 295 words.\n    This is within 200-400.\n\n    Okay, constructing JSON.\n    Make sure to escape double quotes if any. I don't see any double quotes in the text.\n    Make sure to use \\n for line breaks.\n    Make sure key_findings is